{"name":"Wall Walker","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Wall walker&nbsp;</em>allows the recepient to walk on vertical or horizontal surfaces. With @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success}, she moves at half her normal @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace}. With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, she may move at full @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} and even @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{run}.</p>\n<p>If forced to make an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll to climb or hang on to the a surface, she adds +4 to the total.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (&ndash;1/&ndash;3/&ndash;5):</strong>&nbsp;Each additional individual target incurs an additional &minus;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}, or &minus;3 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template}, or &minus;5 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"–1","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"1 min/Rank","trapping":"Spider-like visage, prickly hairs on hands and feet","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"9amN5EFBl5SJIpX6"}
{"name":"Creation","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Creation </em>allows the hero to create a non-magical, unattended object of nonliving vegatable matter. The volume of the object created cannot exceed 1 cubic foot per @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{rank}. It can't rely on intricate artistry or complex moving parts, never fulfills a cost or the like, and can't be made of precious materials or materials with a rarity of uncommon or higher.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Complexity (&ndash;4): </strong>For a &ndash;4 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}, the hero can create an item that has modest artistry and modestly complex moving parts.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"−3","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"1 hour/Rank","trapping":"Hands waving, animating a set of tools.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_9ssl07b3tk","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"9daG3DFOkOEnySNL"}
{"name":"Beast Friend","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This spell allows an individual to speak with and guide the actions of nature&rsquo;s beasts. The cost to cast is equal to the sum of their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} (minimum 1 per creature). Controlling five @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-bestiary.Dog / Wolf]{wolves} (Size &minus;1) costs 5 points (remember the minimum cost of 1), for example. Controlling a rhino (Size 5) costs 5 points.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} means the creatures obey simple commands, like a well-trained dog. They attack foes and endanger their lives for their master. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on the arcane skill roll means the beasts are more obedient. They won&rsquo;t kill themselves but overcome their natural fears to follow their orders.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-bestiary.Swarm]{Swarms} can also be controlled. Small Swarms cost 1 point, Medium Swarms cost 2, and Large Swarms cost 3.</p>\n<p><em> Beast friend</em> works only on natural creatures with animal intelligence, not humanoids, and has no effect on conjured, magical, or otherwise &ldquo;unnatural&rdquo; animals.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Mind Rider (&ndash;1):</strong> The caster can communicate and sense through any of the beasts they've befriended.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"Special","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"10 min/Rank","trapping":"The caster concentrates and gestures with his hands.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"AC19oUmAktVlelvJ"}
{"name":"Animate War Tree","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>War trees are semi-sentient, animated trees, created usually only in desperate times of need.</p>\n<p>With a success, the hero awakens one tree (which must be taller than 30') he is touching as a war tree. On a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the animated tree is a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}. At the end of the spell's duration, the war tree transforms back into a regular tree. If the war tree is killed before this time, the spell is automatically ended.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Heroic","pp":"−10","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"1 hour/Rank","trapping":"Tree becomes covered in runes, warps into a \"tree man.\"","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{"referencedBy":{"JournalEntry":["sKhNmxA2MdN4p4As"]}},"cf":{"id":"temp_2npvrmyhs6y","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Heroic","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"BLx1klFZac5f8smm"}
{"name":"Puppet","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Puppet </em>is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} of the character&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. With @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success}, the victim automatically obeys commands that don&rsquo;t directly harm himself or those he cares about.</span></p>\n<p>With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the target is completely controlled, but gets an automatic @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} to avoid directly arming himself or those he cares about. If the </span><em>puppet</em>&rsquo;s resistance @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{succeeds}, he doesn&rsquo;t carry out that </span>particular command but doesn&rsquo;t otherwise resist his master. With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, he breaks the controller&rsquo;s hold and the power ends.<br /></span></p>\n<p>Commands are general, such as &ldquo;attack that person&rdquo; or &ldquo;open that door.&rdquo; The controller doesn&rsquo;t get to dictate how many @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{actions} the victim uses in a turn, whether or not he uses his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Sweep]{Sweep} Edge, etc.</span></p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</span></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (&ndash;2/&ndash;4/&ndash;6):</strong>&nbsp;Each additional individual target incurs an additional &minus;2 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}, or &minus;4 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template}, or &minus;6 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"–1","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"1 min/Rank","trapping":"Glowing eyes, trance-like state, a swinging pocket watch, voodoo dolls.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_fstj95zcw9j","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"CxFH6Cr0SAFZqNpu"}
{"name":"False Health","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>While this spell does not actually heal, it does allow a character to disregard pain and its symptoms temporarily. With success, the target ignores up to 2 points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} and 1 point of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} penalties, or 4/2 points on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (&ndash;1/&ndash;3/&ndash;5):</strong>&nbsp;Each additional individual target incurs an additional &minus;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}, or &minus;3 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template}, or &minus;5 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"–1","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"1 min/Rank","trapping":"Illusion, mesmerism, ointments, pain reduction.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"EkK1nRLtX36TtWuk"}
{"name":"Object Reading","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Object reading </em>is the ability to see the past of an inanimate object, discovering who held it, where it&rsquo;s been, and what it might have been used for. The object has no sentience of its own &mdash; the caster simply sees and hears visions of the past that took place in its presence.</span></p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} allows the character to see events that occurred within 10 yards up to about five years past. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} increases this to 100 years and 20 yards. The caster can &ldquo;fast forward&rdquo; and &ldquo;rewind&rdquo; as desired, skimming about 10 years of history per minute of real time.</span></p>\n<p>When watching an actual event, it occurs in real time, just as if watching a digital video.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Strong (&ndash;2):</strong> The caster can see or hear from the item's creation forward.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"–2","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","trapping":"Touching the object, glowing hands","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_9ssl07b3tk","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Erw3Oz9YDq7I8uw7"}
{"name":"Intangibility","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll, whoever receives this power becomes incorporeal. He is unable to affect the physical world, and it cannot affect him. He can travel through walls, and non-magical weapons pass straight through him. Any items carried at the time of casting are also incorporeal.</p>\n<p>While incorporeal, the character may affect other incorporeal beings (including himself), and he is still susceptible to supernatural attacks, including @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Powers]{powers} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Devices]{enchanted items}. The being becomes corporeal when the power ends, but if within someone or something he&rsquo;s shunted to the nearest open space and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{Stunned}.</p>\n<p>If cast on an unwilling target, the victim @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{resists} with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Heroic","pp":"–5","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"1 min/Rank","trapping":"Ghost form, body of shadow, gaseous transformation","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_2npvrmyhs6y","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Heroic","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"FRoUKueATNnF9yoq"}
{"name":"Becalm","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Becalm</em> affects a single sailed-ship of any size, halving its @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Vehicle Notes]{Top Speed} for the duration. A ship may be affected by multiple castings of this spell, though neither @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Vehicle Notes]{Top Speed} nor @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Vehicle Notes]{Acceleration} may ever be reduced below 1. It has no effect on oared vessels.</p>\n<p><em>Becalm </em>also adds +2 to a ship's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Boating]{Boating} totals in a storm, whether magical or natural.</p>\n<p>The caster suffers a penalty to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll equal to one-quarter of the ship's base @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness} (ignore Armor), rounded down.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Strong (&ndash;1): </strong>For each &ndash;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}, the elementalist&nbsp;can offset one penalty point for the size of the ship.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"Special","damage":"","range":"Sm x miles","duration":"1 hour/Rank","trapping":"Caster stands on deck and sucks in air, arcane gestures, runes.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_9ssl07b3tk","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"FnIZfxV8GPKG2mz6"}
{"name":"Accelerate Healing","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The power accelerates the target's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Healing]{natural healing} &nbsp;rate. With a successful casting the target may make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Healing]{natural healing} roll once every 24 hour period, with a +2 bonus if cast with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. With a success, the target also gains a +2 bonus to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} rolls for resisting @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Poison]{poison} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Disease]{disease} during the same time, and a +4 bonus with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. The target may only be affected by one casting of accelerate healing at a time.</p>\n<p><strong>Rank:</strong> @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Veteran}<br />@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"−2","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"24 hours","trapping":"Mystical sense, spiritual advice, gestalt knowledge","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_fstj95zcw9j","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"FvtWK7GpDTepjOoh"}
{"name":"Legerdemain","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Legerdemain </em>allows the character to perform a single @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{action} at range he would normally be capable of doing in person. If the action would require a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.eKNM8zLf1AoL2tmj]{Trait roll}, then the caster rolls the lower of that @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} or his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} to both activate the power and determine the results of the action. If the action does not require a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} roll, then his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} is used normally.</p>\n<p>Casting <em>legerdemain </em>is a normal @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{action}, but the action performed through the use of it is considered a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} (existing free actions like speaking are unchanged). However the caster is still limited to not duplicating the same action in a round, so it is impossible to cast another spell via <em>legerdemain</em>.</p>\n<p>The power does not create or duplicate the effects of any gear or magical effects upon the caster, but in all other ways, the action is treated exactly as if the caster were performing the action himself at the location. For example, a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack does his normal unarmed @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} damage, even if the caster is holding a dagger with <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Smite]{smite}</em> on it.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"–1","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Mimicking action, briefly summoned spirit, astral bi-location.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"GEYcwFizERQwMNfA"}
{"name":"Entangle","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Entangle </em>allows the caster to restrain a target with ice, bands of energy, or other vine-like @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trappings]{Trappings} (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Breaking Things]{Hardness} 5). </span>If successful, the target is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bound and Entangled]{Entangled}. With a raise, he&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bound and Entangled]{Bound}.</p>\n<p>Victims may break free on their turn as detailed under @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bound and Entangled]{Bound and Entangled}.</span></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (&ndash;1/&ndash;2):</strong>&nbsp;For a &ndash;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier} the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For a &ndash;2 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier} the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li><strong>Strong (&ndash;2):</strong> The <em>entangling</em> material is particularly resilient. Rolls to break free are made at &ndash;2 and it's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Breaking Things]{Hardness} increases to 7.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"–1","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Glue bomb, vines, handcuffs, webs.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"GeOF44AbYNygGT4Y"}
{"name":"Fly","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Fly </em>allows a character to soar at @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} 12&Prime;, or twice that with a raise (he may not @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Run}).</span></p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</span></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (&ndash;2/&ndash;4/&ndash;6):</strong> Each additional individual target incurs an additional &minus;2 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}, or &minus;4 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template}, or &minus;6 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"–2","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"1 min/Rank","trapping":"Gusty winds, wings, broomsticks","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_fstj95zcw9j","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"H2r6YFv1MekwOH45"}
{"name":"Teleport","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Teleport </em>allows a character to disappear and instantly reappear up to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} x5 miles distant, or double that with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. Teleporting to an unseen location incurs a -4 penalty on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll.</p>\n<p>Opponents adjacent to a character who teleports away don't get a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Free Attacks]{free attack} (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Withdrawing from Melee]{Withdrawing from Melee}).</p>\n<p>If casting <em>teleport </em>on a willing subject, the caster decides where they move to, not the target.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Distance (&ndash;2): </strong>The caster may double the distance traveled.</li>\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (&ndash;1/&ndash;3/&ndash;5):</strong>&nbsp;Each additional individual target incurs an additional &minus;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}, or &minus;3 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template}, or &minus;5 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li><strong>Teleport Foe (&ndash;3):</strong> Foes may be targeted by a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Touch Attack]{Touch attack}. This is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{action}, so the casting must be the second part of a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multi-Actions]{Multi-Action} if the attack is successful. The foe resists the casting with an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll against the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} total and is sent up to 12\" away with success and 24\" with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. Foes may not be teleported into solid objects.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"–6","damage":"","range":"Self","duration":"Instant","trapping":"A cloud of smoke, “phasing” out, change into a bolt of lightning.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_9ssl07b3tk","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"HHGHgTXkni7zwvj7"}
{"name":"Jet","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Jet </em>creates a damaging stream that shoots out from the caster. Measure a straight line 1\" wide and 12\" long starting from the character's position. If successful, targets within this area must make an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} roll versus the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll or suffer 2d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage]{damage}, or 3d6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Damage (&ndash;2):</strong>&nbsp;The&nbsp;<em>jet</em> causes 3d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{damage} (4d6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"−2","damage":"2d6","range":"12\"","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Lightning bolt, battering ram of pure force, rolling ball of fire.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_9ssl07b3tk","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"HV0dF84yvpF74RSi"}
{"name":"Fortune's Favored","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Some heroes are born with a manifest destiny; others need a hand in avoiding an early fate.</p>\n<p>With a successful @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll, a target of this spell that spends a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{benny} and fails the reroll, may immediately make another reroll without having to spend an additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{benny}. Only one free roll per @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{benny} is allowed. If the second roll fails, the hero must spend another @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{benny} to reroll again.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"−2","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"10 min/Rank","trapping":"Victim glows briefly, catches glimpses of future events, sharing of lucky trinket.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_9ssl07b3tk","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Hm4pjK4RPrCOL4qo"}
{"name":"Summon Fiend","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Most heroes would never seek to consort with the denizens of Khyber or Shavarath. But occasionally, such a feat may be required.</p>\n<p>The cost to summon a demon is equal to its @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}&nbsp; die, or twice its @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} die if it's a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card} (most powerful demons are).</p>\n<p>If the roll is successful, the demon appears. If the creature was not summoned into a summoning circle or other binding, it likely attacks its caster before it can be given a task. See page 30 for binding the demon through occult means, and the <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bind Entity]{bind entity}</em> spell for trapping it with arcane power.</p>\n<p><strong>Tasks: </strong>Once a demon is summoned, and assuming it is bound or otherwise disposed to discussion, the summoner must make a bargain with it. This is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} test of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirits}. Record the results secretly.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Failure:</em> The demon is uncontrolled and in complete control of its actions. It cannot directly harm the caster but is otherwise free to roam the earth and do as it pleases for 6d6 days. If it happens to roll three 6's on this roll (no more, no less), it remains in the mortal world until slain or banished.</li>\n<li><em>Success:</em> The demon basically follows the instructions it's given but looks for every opportunity to ruin things for the cretin who summoned it. Only if directly chastised or supervised does the demon \"behave.\"</li>\n<li><em>Raise: </em>The demon follows the spirit of the summoner's instructions as well as the letter. It may still cause additional mayhem-it is a demon, after all-but in general it performs as the caster desires.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Casting Time: </strong>The casting time to summon a demon is one minute per point of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifiers}.</p>\n<p><strong>Specialized Demons:</strong> Some demons might only answer specific requests. A demon of vengeance, for example, may only be tasked with exacting vengeance of some sort. This is entirely up to the Game Master, the setting, and the description of the creature.</p>\n<p><strong>Communication:</strong> Note that demons are not (generally) telepathic. If the summoner plans on sending the demon out of sight, he'd best give it very specific instructions. Intelligent demons may be given physical equipment (such as cell phones or transmitters in modern settings), but whether or not they actually use these tools is entirely up to them.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Horror Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"Special","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"2 hours/Rank","trapping":"Pentagrams, black candles, animal sacrifices.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_fstj95zcw9j","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"IARrHwp4FCHCxWIz"}
{"name":"Elemental Form","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Powerful elementalists have a strong link to the elemental realms, and can convert their own body into elemental matter, if only for a short while.</p>\n<p>For the duration of the spell, the caster gains the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Elemental]{Elemental} of the appropriate elemental type. He retains his own @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{traits}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Edges]{Edges}, and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size}.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"–5","damage":"","range":"Self","duration":"1 min/Rank","trapping":"Bit of element to be changed into, tattoos.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_fstj95zcw9j","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"LEzhr2Gz7hEexakj"}
{"name":"Gift of Battle","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Gift of battle </em>grants the target tactical insight and leadership qualities.</p>\n<p>Success allows the recipient to pick one Leadership Edge. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} means he can take two Edges. He need not meet any requirements except those of other Edges. For instance, the hero cannot gain @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.UKNT4ZWfFCYHbD6V]{Fervor} unless he scores a raise and takes @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.jl9QT69V3DzHS2bq]{Command} first, or already has the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.jl9QT69V3DzHS2bq]{Command} Edge.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"–2","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"1 min/Rank","trapping":"Battle cry, rallying speech, tactical insight.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"LKyd4AkP6vhDqvxQ"}
{"name":"Damage Field","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Damage field </em>creates a dangerous aura around </span>the recipient that harms foes foolish enough to get too close.<br /></span></p>\n<p>At the end of the affected character's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{turn}, all adjacent beings (including allies!) automatically take 2d4 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{damage}.</span></p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</span></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Damage (&ndash;2):</strong> The <em>damage field</em> causes 2d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{damage}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"–3","damage":"2d4","range":"Sm","duration":"1 min/Rank","trapping":"Fiery aura, spikes, electrical field","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_9ssl07b3tk","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"LNVI7hMh57XBpH1E"}
{"name":"Analyze Foe","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Knowledge is power. Being able to judge the strength of a foe before engaging him in combat can be highly advantageous.</p>\n<p>The character makes an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by the target's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. On a success, he gains a +1 bonus to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} rolls to directly affect the target, and the target suffers a &ndash;1 penalty to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} rolls to directly affect the caster. With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the effect is increased to +2 and &ndash;2 for both.</p>\n<p><strong>Rank:</strong> @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Novice}<br />@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Information (&ndash;1): </strong>A success allows the caster to learn of a single @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Immunity]{Immunity}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Invulnerability]{Invulnerability}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Weakness]{Weakness} of the target (if one exists), and a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} allows the knowledge of two.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"−1","damage":"","range":"Sm x2","duration":"1 min/Rank","trapping":"Mystical sense, spiritual advice, gestalt knowledge","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"LyqPnwZ2rJjrTigH"}
{"name":"Fear","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This power causes overwhelming dread and horror. The affected make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fear]{Fear} roll. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras} who fail are @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Fear Table]{Panicked} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Cards} roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-macros.Fear Table]{Fear Table}</span>. If the power is cast with a raise, the Fear roll is at -2 and Wild Cards add +2 to Fear Table</span>&nbsp;</span>results.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (&ndash;1/&ndash;3/&ndash;5):</strong>&nbsp;Each additional individual target incurs an additional &minus;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}, or &minus;3 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template}, or &minus;5 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"–1","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Gestures, eldritch energy, cold chills","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"M0Hasj4LLW2ufZ9R"}
{"name":"Healing","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Healing </em>removes @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} </span>less than an hour old. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} removes one Wound, and a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} removes two. The power may be cast additional times to remove additional Wounds within that hour and as long as the healer has enough @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}.</span></p>\n<p>For @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras}, the GM must first determine if the ally is still alive (see </span>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Healing]{Aftermath}). If so, a successful arcane skill roll returns the ally to action (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} </span>if it matters).</span></p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</span></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Greater Healing (&ndash;5):</strong> <em>Greater healing</em> can restore any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}, including those more than an hour old.</li>\n<li><strong>Crippling Injuries (&ndash;10):</strong> The power can heal a permanent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Injury Table]{Crippling Injury} (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitation}). This requires an hour of preparation and only one casting is permitted per injury. If it @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails}, this caster cannot <em>heal </em>that particular injury (but somoene else may try). If successful, the subject is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Exhausted} for 24 hours.</li>\n<li><strong>Neutralize Poison or Disease (&ndash;1):</strong> A successful <em>healing&nbsp;</em>roll negates any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Poison]{poison} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Disease]{disease}. If the poison or disease has a bonus or penalty associated with it, the modifier applies to the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll as well.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"–2","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Laying on hands, touching the victim with a holy symbol, prayer","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"M12n9FdqxAjWjsii"}
{"name":"Stun","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Stun </em>shocks a target with concussive force, sound, light, magical energy, or the like.</span></p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful} casting means the victim must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} roll (at &ndash;2 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll) or be @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{Stunned}.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (&ndash;1/&ndash;2):</strong>&nbsp;For a &ndash;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier} the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For a &ndash;2 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier} the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"–1","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Bolts of energy, stun bombs, sonic booms, burst of blinding light","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"M9DIgOTBbtsh8SJJ"}
