{"name":"Havoc","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This ability creates chaos and mischief for all those within its area of effect, hurling debris and rivals in all directions.</p>\n<p>With success, the caster places a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template} anywhere within @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{range}, or a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Cone Template} emanating from the caster.</p>\n<p>Anyone touched by the template is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted} and must <em>then </em>make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} roll (at -2 if the caster got a raise). Those who fail are hurled [[/r 2d6]]&Prime;&mdash;directly away from the caster if using the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Cone Template} or directly away from the center if using a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Blast Template} (the caster chooses for those in the dead center).</p>\n<p>Victims who strike a hard object (such as a wall) take [[/r 2d4]] damage (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Nonlethal Damage]{nonlethal} unless it&rsquo;s a spiked wall or other more dangerous hazard).</p>\n<p><strong>Airborne Targets</strong>: </span>Flying or airborne targets suffer an additional &ndash;2 to their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} rolls as they have no ground to brace themselves on.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (&ndash;2):</strong> For a &ndash;2 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier} the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li><strong>Strong (&ndash;2):</strong> @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} rolls are made at &ndash;2</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"–1","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Whirlwind, chaotic poltergeists, repulsion field","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"MvxGxXutKtRNpAYP"}
{"name":"Illusion","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Illusion </em>can be used to create a visual scene or replica of most anything the caster can imagine, but it is silent, intangible, and incapable of affecting the real world. For example, illusionary weapons pass through foes, one cannot sit in an illusionary chair, and an illusionary dog has no audible bark.</span></p>\n<p>Those who contact an </span><em>illusion </em>or doubt it&rsquo;s real make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} roll as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} (at -2 if the power was activated with a raise). If @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful}, that individual is no longer subject to this casting.<br /></span></p>\n<p>The GM should make @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{group rolls} for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras} </span>as they point out the </span><em>illusion&rsquo;s </em>inconsistencies to each other.<br /></span></p>\n<p>The volume of the </span><em>illusion </em>must fit within a sphere the size of a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}</span>&nbsp;(4&Prime; or eight yards in diameter).</span></p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</span></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Sound (&ndash;1):</strong> The power generates sound appropriate to the <em>Illusion</em>. Illusionary allies may talk, illusionary crows caw, and so on. It may not mask or mute existing sound, however.&nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>Strong (&ndash;2):</strong> @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} rolls to disbelieve the <em>illusion </em>are made at &ndash;2.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"–1","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"1 min/Rank","trapping":"Magical spells, holograms, \"ethereal materializers\"","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"NXJhJ3dHyYaKADFf"}
{"name":"Sloth/Speed","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Sloth </em>lessens celerity and coordination while </span><em>speed </em>increases it. It halves the target&rsquo;s total @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{movement} each @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{round} (round up). With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, movement is also an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{action}. The target automatically attempts to shake off the effects of </span><em>sloth </em>at the end of each of his next turns by making a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll.</span></p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} with </span><em>speed </em>doubles the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{movement} (basic Pace and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{running}</span>). With a&nbsp;</span>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} the character also ignores the -2 running penalty.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (&ndash;1/&ndash;3/&ndash;5):</strong>&nbsp;<em>Speed </em>only. Each additional individual target incurs an additional &minus;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}, or &minus;3 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template}, or &minus;5 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li><em><strong style=\"font-style: normal;\">Area of Effect (&ndash;1/&ndash;2):</strong><span style=\"font-style: normal;\"> </span>Sloth&nbsp;</em>only. For a &ndash;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier} the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For a &ndash;2 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier} the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li><strong>Quickness (&ndash;2):</strong> <em>Speed </em>only. The character's total @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multi-Actions]{Multi-Action} penalty each turn is reduced by 2 (she can do two actions at no penalty, or three at &ndash;2 each).</li>\n<li><strong>Strong (&ndash;2):</strong> <em>Sloth</em> only. The @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll to shake off <em>sloth's&nbsp;</em>effects is made at &ndash;2.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"–2","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"Instant (sloth); 1 min/Rank (speed)","trapping":"Slowing time, blurred motion, a slippery patch of oil or ice","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_9ssl07b3tk","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"O2NjJqw7Jvzr2cCQ"}
{"name":"Banish","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Banish </em>sends entities from immaterial planes back to their native dimensions. This includes ghosts, demons, elementals, and similar beings (at the GM&rsquo;s discretion).</p>\n<p><em>Banishing </em>a being is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} of the caster&rsquo;s arcane skill versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} means the target is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken}, and each @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} causes a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}.</p>\n<p>If this @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitates} the target it returns to its native plane of existence. <em>Banished </em>entities may return when the Game Master feels it&rsquo;s appropriate, such as the next full moon, when summoned again, or even a few rounds later if it&rsquo;s a particularly powerful creature under the right conditions or in a location of power.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"−3","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Holy items, arcane symbols, handful of salt","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_fstj95zcw9j","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"PNEpOmHPvFEggX15"}
{"name":"Ward","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Ward </em>creates an invisible barrier that can keep out one specific type of creature determined when the spell is cast. The target creature type must be chosen from the following monstrous abilities: Aquatic, Burrowing, Construct, Demon, Elemental, Ethereal, Flight, Large/Huge, Plant, Poison, Small (affects swarms as well), or Undead.</p>\n<p>The caster first makes his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll and then places a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template} centered on himself. With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} to the casting roll, the template increases to a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template}. Creatures of the defined type wishing to enter the Template must make an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} check against the caster's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} total. If they fail, they cannot pass the ward while the spell remains active.</p>\n<p><em>Ward </em>stops the entity from passing through, but only weakens their ability to use other monstrous abilities such as @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fear]{Fear} or throwing physical objects. Such abilities or attacks suffer a &ndash;2 penalty against beings in the ward, &ndash;4 if cast with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"–4","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"2 hour/Rank","trapping":"Ring or circle of scented oil or holy water or salt, salt, glyphs, leaves, fragrant wood.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_9ssl07b3tk","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"PNL8offaRopTFOoz"}
{"name":"Grave Speak","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>It is said the dead know many secrets, and through the black arts a mage can reach beyond death to contact departed souls. Though not evil, many good spellcasters avoid using this power for they feel it disturbs those who have earned their rest.</p>\n<p>In order for this spell to work, it must be directed toward a particular soul. The caster must know the full name of the deceased or possess a personal item, which includes their corpse, or any part of it at least, as well as a treasured item.</p>\n<p>If the spell succeeds, a ghostly voice makes itself known and may be questioned. One question may be asked for each round the spell is active.</p>\n<p>The spirit contacted is not necessarily friendly and can lie, but it may not refuse to answer or make guesses. The Dungeon Master must decide what information the entity knows-the spirit is not omnipotent and typically knows only what it knew in life up to the moment of its death.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure}, may summon up a demon or other hostile entity. While these spirits cannot usually affect the caster when contacted in this way (they're not summoned), it may try to convince him it is the person he sought, then feed him inaccurate or dangerous information to lead the character to his death.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Horror Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"–4","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"2 min/Rank","trapping":"Runes carved on bodily remains, black candles, \"leather\" books","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_9ssl07b3tk","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"PQlEOP4kbtxUqkqw"}
{"name":"Zephyr","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This is the spell casters aligned to the wind are most commonly asked to perform. It gently pushes ships along even in a dead calm, and can also improve top speed in normal winds or during deadly combat.</p>\n<p>It can be used to cancel the spell <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.becalm]{becalm}</em>. In combat, <em>zephyr </em>improves a vessel's current @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Vehicle Notes]{Handling} by +1 and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Vehicle Notes]{Top Speed} by 25%. It may be cast multiple times, though base @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Vehicle Notes]{Top Speed} may never be more than doubled.</p>\n<p>Spellcasters have discovered another use for this spell as well. It is quite adept at dispersing swarms of flying pests, such as wasps. A success @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shakes} the swarm, while a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} disperses them (effectively causing a wound). In a few cases, dispersing a swarm actually results in two swarms.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Ships (&ndash;2): </strong>For an additional &ndash;2 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier} another ship can be included in the <em>zephyr </em>wind.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"–1","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"1 hour/Rank","trapping":"The hero stands behind the sails, arms out raised and gently blowing, air elemental billows the sails.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_9ssl07b3tk","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"PXEkucMb3AwpKDWU"}
{"name":"Disguise","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Disguise </em>allows the target to assume the appearance of another person of the same @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} and shape, including clothing. It does not confer any abilities, however.</span></p>\n<p>Those who have reason to question the imposter&rsquo;s identity make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} roll at &ndash;2 to see through the </span><em>disguise </em>(&ndash;4 with a raise on the casting roll). This is a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action}.</span></p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</span></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (&ndash;1/&ndash;3/&ndash;5):</strong>&nbsp;Each additional individual target incurs an additional &minus;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}, or &minus;3 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template}, or &minus;5 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li><strong>Size (&ndash;1):</strong> The recipient may assume the shape of someone up to two @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Sizes}</span> larger or smaller than themselves.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"–1","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"10 min/Rank","trapping":"Malleable features, illusionary appearance, hair of new form","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_9ssl07b3tk","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Q9TlV3tRoXrOdarx"}
{"name":"Magic Mark","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Magic mark </em>can be visible or invisible. If a <em>magic mark </em>was created as a visible mark, a caster can use <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal]{conceal}</em> <em>(arcana) </em>to temporarily hide it. Casting <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal]{detect}</em> <em>(arcana) </em>will reveal a permanent or temporarily concealed <em>magic mark</em>. Casting @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Dispel]{dispel} on an <em>magic mark </em>can remove it permanently.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"–1","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Permenant","trapping":"Mystical tattoos, invisible sigils, arcane runes.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"RYTOf1qLnZqf6D7Q"}
{"name":"Conjure Item","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Conjure item </em>allows a caster to create a minor mundane item weighing less than one pound<em>&mdash;</em>a dagger, a playing card, hand mirror, and so on. With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the Duration is in minutes instead of rounds (and is Maintained in minutes as well if desired).</p>\n<p><em>Conjured items</em> typically appear in a pocket, pouch, or bag to hide the magic that conjures them, but it's not strictly necessary.</p>\n<p>Once the Duration expires, the item fades from reality. If the shyster used conjured coins to buy something, he might be in trouble if the merchant figures out who swindled him.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Deadlands Weird West</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Complete (&ndash;1): </strong>The object is a complete set, though it still must fit under the weight limit. For example, a deck of cards has all 54 cards in it or it is a whole conqueror set, and so on.</li>\n<li><strong>Power (&ndash;1):</strong> For each additional &ndash;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}, the item can weigh up to two additional pounds or twice that with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"–1","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"1 min/Rank","trapping":"Slieght of hand, color spray, minor illusions, wave of hand","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"SCa1lHfvvmPSTYH6"}
{"name":"Bind Entity","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Bind entity</em> allows its user to force an entity into servitude. Any entity that can be summoned can generally be bound. The creature may be summoned and then bound, or it might already be in the physical world.</p>\n<p>The cost to invoke this spell is equal to twice the entity's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} die type. A demon with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} die of d8, for example, requires 16 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} to cast bind entity on it.</p>\n<p>In either case, the caster makes an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} &nbsp;by the entity's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. If the entity is already subject to a <em>bind entity</em> spell it receives a +4 bonus to its roll.</p>\n<p>On a success, the caster has bound the creature to his will for the duration of the spell. The creature must obey commands given to it, both to the letter and spirit, though orders that would undeniably end the entity's existence allow it another roll to break free.</p>\n<p>There is no inherent mental link between the caster and the entity, so commands must be expressed by some method the creature understands.</p>\n<p>The caster may not try to bind the same entity more than once in any 24 hour period, nor may he attempt to bind the same entity for 24 hours after the current binding expires (though he may maintain the spell). The entity does not need to be in Range or even seen to maintain the power.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Horror Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"Special","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"24 hours","trapping":"Chanting, wardings, special substances.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_fstj95zcw9j","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"SDEDtcvwAsqytqHJ"}
{"name":"Leaping","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The target of this spell can @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.ERoL9pRXAZWSSFpF]{jump} greater distances than normal. A success doubles his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{jumping} distances, while a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} quadruples them. Modifiers are applied after running starts are factored in.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"–1","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"1 min/Rank","trapping":"Powerful legs, legs change to an animal's.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"TlcN5fkz7ZbYehOz"}
{"name":"Resurrection","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Perhaps the greatest power of all is the ability to bring someone back from the dead. It can restore lost loves, bring solace to the grieving, and topple kingdoms.</p>\n<p>Returning the dead to life requires a reasonably complete corpse no more than a year old. The caster then prays, meditates, chants, or otherwise concentrates on mending the body and pulling the spirit back to it for four hours.</p>\n<p>Once done, the healer makes a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{casting roll} at &ndash;8. If successful, the victim returns to life with three @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} and is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Exhausted}. With a raise, she returns merely @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Exhausted}.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Power (&ndash;5):</strong> The hero can raise a spirit dead up to a decade for an additional &ndash;5 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Heroic","pp":"–15","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Elaborate ceremonies, rare plants, magical amulets, divine intervention","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_2npvrmyhs6y","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Heroic","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"TuuxPIndG1yzbxSl"}
{"name":"Mind Wipe","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Mind wipe </em>removes a target&rsquo;s memories, a terrible violation in most civilized societies. The power is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by a victim&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} and requires a full minute of mental struggle. The victim must be conscious during this time, so if not restrained he can simply move out of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Range}.</span></p>\n<p>If @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful}, the victim forgets a single event (up to about 30 minutes of time). A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} removes a complex memory of several hours.</span></p>\n<p>If the defender wins, the caster cannot affect him with </span><em>mind wipe </em>for 24 hours. (Others may reattempt the power, however.)<br /></span></p>\n<p>The memory remains missing but strong evidence that challenges its &ldquo;logic&rdquo; allows a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} roll at &ndash;2 to remember fragments determined by the GM.</span></p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</span></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Edit (&ndash;1):</strong> Instead of wiping the memory, the caster edits it as she sees fit.</span></li>\n<li><strong>Fast Cast (&ndash;2):</strong> The caster can wipe a memory as an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{action}.</span></li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"–5","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"Instant","trapping":"A noxious drink, parasites, touching the target's temples","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_fstj95zcw9j","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"UwI41NOsvoAtcUln"}
{"name":"Deflection","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Deflection </em>powers work in a variety of ways. Some manifestations actually </span>deflect incoming @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Attacks]{attacks}, others blur the target&rsquo;s form or produce illusionary effects. The end result is always the same, however&mdash;to misdirect incoming melee and missile @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Attacks]{attacks}&nbsp;from the recipient of the power.</span></p>\n<p>Once cast, foes must subtract 2 from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Attacks]{attack} rolls directed at the user (or 4 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}).</span></p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</span></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (&ndash;1/&ndash;3/&ndash;5):</strong> Each additional individual target incurs an additional &minus;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}, or &minus;3 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template}, or &minus;5 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"–2","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"1 min/Rank","trapping":"Mystical shield, gust of wind, phantom servant that intercepts missiles","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Vfh2p3hnB9eSfAhv"}
{"name":"Growth/Shrink","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Growth </em>increases the recipient&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} by 1 for every&nbsp;</span>&ndash;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier} incurred. Each increase in </span>Size</span> grants the target a one-step increase to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} and 1 point of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness}.</span> This does not increase @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wounds} regardless of change to </span>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale}</span>.</span></p>\n<p><em>Shrink </em>reduces the </span>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size}</span> of the subject one step for every&nbsp;</span>&ndash;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}incurred to a maximum of Size&nbsp;</span>&ndash;2 (approximately the size of a cat). Each step reduced decreases @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} one die type (minimum of d4) and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness} by 1 (minimum of 2).</p>\n<p>For unwilling targets, the caster&rsquo;s arcane skill roll is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}.</span></p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"Special","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"10 min/Rank","trapping":"Gestures, words of power, potions","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_9ssl07b3tk","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"gm-notes":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"W1WBgq9fkNKN8mjD"}
{"name":"Feast","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The character creates enough food and water for three humanoids or one mount for 24 hours. The food and water appear on the ground or in containers within range. The food is bland but nourishing, and spoils if uneaten after 24 hours. The water is clean and doesn't go bad.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (&ndash;1/&ndash;3/&ndash;5):</strong>&nbsp;Each additional individual target incurs an additional &minus;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}, or &minus;3 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template}, or &minus;5 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li><strong>Feast (&ndash;6): </strong>For an additional &ndash;6 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier} the food is not bland but the quality of a multi-course feast meal. Rather than water, any kind of drink of the hero's choice is created.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"−3","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"24 hour","trapping":"Animating cooking utensils, waving hands over a table.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_9ssl07b3tk","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"WGlVNHB6wImcuBfe"}
{"name":"Burst","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Burst </em>produces a large fan of energy that bathes its targets in red-hot fire, a cone of cold, or other damaging matter or energy.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} creates a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Cone Template} starting at the caster and extending outward. Everything within suffers 2d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage]{damage} (or 3d6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Damage (&ndash;2):</strong> The <em>burst</em> causes 3d6 damage, or 4d6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"−1","damage":"2d6","range":"Cone Template","duration":"Instant","trapping":"A shower of flames, light or other matter of energy.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"WMzfwzJnXsHqu2Qo"}
{"name":"Relief","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Relief </em>removes one @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} level, or two with a raise. It can also remove a character&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} </span>status, and removes @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{Stunned} status with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</span></p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</span></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (&ndash;1/&ndash;3/&ndash;5):</strong>&nbsp;Each additional individual target incurs an additional &minus;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}, or &minus;3 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template}, or &minus;5 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"–1","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Prayer, tonics","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Xi5vSCbvvjV1Kon1"}
{"name":"Battle Song","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This spell, beloved of warlike bards, skalds and dirgesingers, causes the targets to fly into a battle frenzy.</p>\n<p>Every creature within a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template} centered on the caster, apart from the caster, is granted the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Berserk]{Berserk} Edge for the duration of the spell. On a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the targets immediately go berserk, as per the Edge. Unwilling recipients are allowed a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by the caster's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} &nbsp;to resist. This spell affects friends and foe alike.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (&ndash;2):</strong> For a &ndash;2 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier} the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"−1","damage":"","range":"Special","duration":"1 min/Rank","trapping":"Poetry, battle chant.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_9ssl07b3tk","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"YufSABz53bHXixDA"}
{"name":"Message","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Message </em>can allow the wizard to deliver a message of up to twenty-five words, or fifty words with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, to a creature in which the wizard is familiar with. The recipient recognizes the sender if it knowns them, and can answer the message in a like manner.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>More Words (&ndash;1/&ndash;3):</strong> The caster can increase the number of words within the message doubling them for an additional &minus;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier} or quadrupling them for an additional &minus;3 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}.</li>\n<li><strong>Unknown Recipient (&ndash;2):</strong> For an additional &minus;2 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}&nbsp;the caster can send a message to a recipient that he is not familiar with provided the caster knows something that can identify the recipient.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"–1","damage":"","range":"Sm x2 miles","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Whispered message to an animal, message delivered on the wind.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_9ssl07b3tk","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"aEVOaP30I4j0cU5t"}
{"name":"Dimensional Leap","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>This is a renaming of the Teleport Power.</em></p>\n<p><em>Dimensional leap </em>allows a character to disappear and instantly reappear up to 12\"; (24 yards) distant, or double that with a raise. Teleporting to an unseen location incurs a -2 penalty on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll.</p>\n<p>Opponents adjacent to a character who teleports away don't get a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Free Attacks]{free attack} (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Withdrawing from Melee]{Withdrawing from Melee} ).</p>\n<p>If casting <em>dimensional leap </em>on a willing subject, the caster decides where they move to, not the target.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Modified from Savage Worlds Adventure Edition</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Distance (&ndash;2): </strong>The caster may double the distance traveled.</li>\n<li><strong>Move Foe (&ndash;2): </strong>Foes may be targeted by a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Touch Attack]{Touch attack}. This is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{action}, so the casting must be the second part of a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multi-Actions]{Multi-Action} if the attack is successful. The foe resists the casting with an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll against the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} total and is sent up to 12\" away with success and 24\" with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. Foes may not be teleported into solid objects.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"–1","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"Instant","trapping":"A cloud of smoke, \"phasing\" out, change into a bolt of lightning.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_9ssl07b3tk","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ar0J3aveYCA5TgSd"}
{"name":"Whirlwind","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>By making an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll, the dragonmarked creates a <em>whirlwind</em>.</p>\n<p>The whirlwind fills a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template} placed anywhere within range. Anything coming into contact with it must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} roll or be knocked prone, at &minus;2 on a raise. The target's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} also modifies this roll. Thus, dragons are harder to knock over than halflings.</p>\n<p>The caster can move the whirlwind up to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} die in inches each round, but doing so is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{action}.</p>\n<p>If the center of the whirlwind is moved out of the caster's line of sight, the spell is automatically ended.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Area Effect (0/&ndash;2):</strong> The caster can focus the <em>whirlwind</em> to a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Small Blast Template} for no additional Casting Modifier, or for &minus;2 everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template} is effected.</li>\n<li><strong>Strong (&ndash;2): </strong>The @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} roll to resist the whirlwind's effects is made at &ndash;2.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"–1","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"1 min/Rank","trapping":"Exhaling, using a fan, spinning motion.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_9ssl07b3tk","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"b2HxC8r0WwwNkW84"}
{"name":"Arcane Protection","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} with arcane protection means hostile powers suffer a &minus;2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalty} (&minus;4 with a raise) to affect this character.</p>\n<p>If the power causes harm, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{damage} is also reduced a like amount. Arcane Protection stacks with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Arcane Resistance]{Arcane Resistance} should the recipient have both!</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (&ndash;1/&ndash;3/&ndash;5):</strong>&nbsp;Each additional individual target incurs an additional &minus;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}, or &minus;3 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template}, or &minus;5 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"1 min/Rank","trapping":"Concentration, a dull glow around the protected character, a fetish","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"bLz8gdRcKNIx524p"}
{"name":"Holy Symbol","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Evil creatures find it hard to attack a devout follower with true faith&mdash;and a symbol of her deity to back it up.</p>\n<p>Once invoked, any supernaturally evil creature (Dungeon Master's call) that wants to make a direct, physical attack on the bearer of the symbol must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} (the creature subtracts 2 if the faithful cast with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}).</p>\n<p>Attacks include @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{area effect attacks} that would catch the bearer in their template, but wouldn't affect knocking a shelf over to land on the bearer, for example. <em>Holy symbol</em> has no effect on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Tests} or other nondamaging attacks.</p>\n<p>The faithful must have an actual holy symbol to invoke the miracle. No holy symbol, no <em>holy symbol</em>.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (&ndash;1/&ndash;2):</strong>&nbsp;For a &ndash;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier} the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For a &ndash;2 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier} the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li><strong>Strong (&minus;2):</strong> @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} rolls by the creature are made at &minus;2 (&minus;4 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"–1","damage":"","range":"Self","duration":"1 min/Rank","trapping":"Presenting holy symbol, calling in divine guidance","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"bc2RRRNO8ce0tMpn"}
{"name":"Mind Rider","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>A character can use this ability to sense through another, including sight, taste, touch, scent, and sound.</p>\n<p>If the subject is willing, the caster simply makes an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill}. If not, the target may make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll to resist (at -2 if the caster got a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} total). If the target succeeds with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the power fails and he knows he was targeted by magic.</p>\n<p>A successful casting allows the character to sense through all his victim's senses. The Range is only limited when the power is activated&mdash;it remains no matter how the target moves afterward.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Deadlands Weird West</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Mind Rider (&ndash;2): </strong>The character can cast this spell on an unseen target up to 50 miles distant if he has an object the subject touched within the last week, or that was precious to him in some way.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"–2","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"1 hour/Rank","trapping":"Trance, runes on face, face of caster superimposed with that of target.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_9ssl07b3tk","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"c0nu7H1dJrmSwUlv"}
