{"name":"Blind","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Those affected by this malicious power suffer blurred vision or near-complete blindness </span>with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} means the victim suffers a&nbsp;&ndash;2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalty} to all actions requiring sight, or &ndash;4 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</p>\n<p>The victim automatically tries to shake off the effect with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} roll as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of his following turns.&nbsp;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} removes 2 points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalties}, and a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} removes the effect entirely.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (&ndash;1/&ndash;2):</strong> For a &ndash;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier} the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For a &ndash;2 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier} the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li><strong>Strong (&ndash;2):</strong> The @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} roll to shake of the effect is made at &ndash;2.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"−2","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Bright flash of light, sand in eyes, confusion","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"fcN63remCicfvbS2"}
{"name":"Speak Language","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This power allows a character to speak, read, and write a sapient language other than his own. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll allows the user to appropriately use and understand slang and dialect as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (&ndash;1/&ndash;3/&ndash;5):</strong>&nbsp;Each additional individual target incurs an additional &minus;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}, or &minus;3 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template}, or &minus;5 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"–1","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"1 hour/Rank","trapping":"Words, pictures, hand motions","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"g2QVrQUqOAkFgpcu"}
{"name":"Dimensional Space","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Dimensional space</em> allows the hero to create an extradimensional space that is the space of two 10 foot cubes, that can hold up to eight creatures. The entrance to the space can be any kind of portal chosen in the trapping.</p>\n<p>Attacks and spells cannot cross through the entrance into or out of the extradimensional space. If the occupants of the space can see out into the outside world, then the outside world can also see into the dimensional space.</p>\n<p>The space does not include anything, but if anything is left when the spell ends, the items drop out of the <em>dimensional space</em>.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (&ndash;1):</strong> Each additional individual target incurs an additional &minus;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}.</li>\n<li><strong>Additional Size (<strong>&ndash;</strong>1): </strong>The power may double the size of the space for each additional @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}.</li>\n<li><strong>Additional Time (&ndash;3/&ndash;5): </strong>The space may last up to eight hours for a &ndash;3 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}, or up to 24 hours for a &ndash;5 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}.</li>\n<li><strong>Food and Drink (&ndash;3): </strong>The space can be furnished with enough food and drink for each occupant with a basic but nutritious meal.</li>\n<li><strong>Magnificent Mansion (&ndash;10): </strong>The power may add food and water to feed all the occupants of the space with a lavish meal. It will include one near-transparent servant for each occupant in the space. The space can be divided up into various lavishly appointed chambers to the desire of the hero.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"–2","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"1 hour","trapping":"A rope climbed into a hidden space in the sky, door appears free standing, mystical portal.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_9ssl07b3tk","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"gDgwXuCqw0dDXS03"}
{"name":"Invisibility","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success}, the character and his personal items are transparent except for a vague blur or outline. Any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{action} taken against him that requires sight is made at &ndash;4, or &ndash;6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. The same penalty applies to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls to detect the unseen presence.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (&ndash;3/&ndash;5/&ndash;7):</strong> Each additional individual target incurs an additional &minus;3 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}, or &minus;5 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template}, or &minus;7 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"–3","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"1 min/Rank","trapping":"Powder, potion, iridescent lights","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_9ssl07b3tk","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"gO4VsB0Q3FrkRNv8"}
{"name":"Environmental Protection","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Adventurers sometimes travel beneath the waves, in space, or other hazardous environments. This power protects them from crushing depths, scathing heat, intense cold, and even radiation.</span></p>\n<p><em>Environmental protection </span></em>allows the target to breathe, speak, and move at his normal @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace}</span> in an otherwise fatal environment. It protects him against intense @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Heat]{heat}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cold]{cold}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Radiation]{radiation}, atmospheric or fluid pressure, and lack of oxygen. Generally, the adventurer can function normally underwater, in space, within the cone of a volcano, etc. It fails quickly (1d4 rounds) in the presence of super-intense conditions such as actual lava or the massive radiation of a melting nuclear core, for example.</span></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (&ndash;1/&ndash;3/&ndash;5):</strong>&nbsp;Each additional individual target incurs an additional &minus;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}, or &minus;3 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template}, or &minus;5 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"–1","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"1 hour/Rank","trapping":"A mark on the forehead, potions, gills.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"h5t0ckuZW6xAwx0t"}
{"name":"Sentry","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Getting a good night's sleep in the middle of orc country is easier said than done. Sentry duty is tiring and lonely, and a single sentry nodding off can spell disaster. <em>Sentry </em>provides additional security for the wary traveler. It can also be used to safeguard valuables.</p>\n<p>The first version of this spell creates a ghostly sentry who watches over the camp but cannot move further away from the caster than the caster's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} x 2 in game inches. The sentry has a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} of d8, or d10 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, is always alert, and suffers no penalties for bad lighting. Despite being visible as a ghostly form, the <em>sentry </em>is not a physical manifestation and cannot be harmed, though it can be dispelled .</p>\n<p>The <em>sentry </em>may be given instructions on when to sound the alarm but it is not an intelligent, reasoning being. Instructions may contain no more than 10 words and must be clearly defined. For the purposes of identifying potential threats, the sentry has the same knowledge of monsters and hazards as the caster.</p>\n<p>The second variant protects a single object touched by the caster when he invokes the spell. During the casting, the spellcaster may name a number of individuals equal to half his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} die type who can safely touch the object. Anyone else touching it immediately activates the spell, which alerts the caster to the tampering.</p>\n<p>The spell automatically expires at sunset or sunrise, whichever occurs first, and the caster may even sleep while the spell is active. It counts as Maintained.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"–3","damage":"","range":"Sm x 2","duration":"Special","trapping":"Circle of chalk, powder, or blood, mystic rune, staff thrust into ground.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_9ssl07b3tk","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"iePbltFq6hH6c3mq"}
{"name":"Warrior's Gift","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll, the recipient gains the benefits of a single Combat @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edge} chosen by the caster. The caster (not the recipient) must have the same @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank} or higher as the Edge&rsquo;s Requirements. With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the recipient gains the Improved version of the Edge (if there is one, and even if he doesn&rsquo;t meet the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Rank Requirement}).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (&ndash;1/&ndash;3/&ndash;5):</strong>&nbsp;Each additional individual target incurs an additional &minus;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}, or &minus;3 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template}, or &minus;5 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"–3","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"1 min/Rank","trapping":"Gestures, prayer, whispered words, concentration","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_9ssl07b3tk","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ik2csD4xe8toTlzt"}
{"name":"Darksight","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Darksight </em>allows a hero to see in the dark. With success, he ignores up to 4 points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination penalties}. With a raise, he ignores up to six points and can see in @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{pitch darkness}.</span></p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</span></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (&ndash;1/&ndash;3/&ndash;5):</strong>&nbsp;Each additional individual target incurs an additional &minus;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}, or &minus;3 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template}, or &minus;5 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"–2","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"1 hour/Rank","trapping":"Glowing eyes, dilated pupils, sonic sight","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ixoFFcc3nktILX4m"}
{"name":"Divination","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Divination </em>allows the caster to contact otherworldly beings or forces to gain information.</span></p>\n<p>Preparing the spell takes one uninterrupted minute, and must be done at a site relevant to the spirit being contacted. If speaking with a ghost, for example, the conversation should occur at its grave, where it was killed, or with a personal object in hand. Oracles may only be engaged at temples, fire spirits near open flames, and so on.</span></p>\n<p>After the preparation time is complete, the caster makes her arcane skill roll. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} allows her to engage with the spirit and ask it any questions she might have. The entity must answer to the best of its ability, as directly or ambiguously as the Game Master feels fits the spirit&rsquo;s personality and the feel of her campaign. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} means the spirit is more helpful, knowledgeable, or direct than usual (whether it wants to be or not). </span>The type of entity contacted determines how it communicates. Spirits in the netherworld tend to know only those things pertinent to their life and death&mdash;and they may not even know the identity of their killer if the person was masked or unseen.</span></p>\n<p>Likewise, nature spirits know only about their local environs, demons know only about the affairs they&rsquo;re directly involved in, and so on. The Game Master must decide what the entity knows based on its background, origin, and personality. </span>Once a spirit has been conversed with it may not be contacted again for 24 hours. The Game Master may extend this to a community of spirits in a single place, such as water spirits in a babbling brook or nameless spirits in a mass grave.</span></p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Heroic","pp":"–6","damage":"","range":"Self","duration":"A brief conversation of about five minutes","trapping":"Seances, prayers, demonic interrogation.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_2npvrmyhs6y","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Heroic","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"jQPbc3bwjcDuVUS4"}
{"name":"Summon Elemental","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This powerful spell enables a mage to summon a living spirit of his chosen element&mdash;an \"elemental.\" The creature is completely subject to the whims of the caster.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Mind Rider (&ndash;1):</strong> The caster can communicate and sense through the ally.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"–5","damage":"","range":"Special","duration":"10 min/Rank","trapping":"A bit of raw element-a hand full of earth, a flame, water or breath of air.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_fstj95zcw9j","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"jR2ZbibnfKpLPmVf"}
{"name":"Blast","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Blast</em> launches a ball of explosive energy or matter. The area of effect is a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. Every target within suffers 2d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage]{damage}, or 3d6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Area Effect Attacks}).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (&ndash;0/&ndash;1):</strong>&nbsp;For no @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}&nbsp;<em>blast</em> affects everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Small Blast Template}. For a &ndash;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier} the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li><strong>Damage (&ndash;2):</strong>&nbsp;The&nbsp;<em>blast</em>&nbsp;causes 3d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{damage} (4d6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"−2","damage":"2d6","range":"Sm x 2","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Balls of fire, ice, light, darkness, colored bolts, swarm of insects","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_9ssl07b3tk","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"jzoOsazN5tF8L9EA"}
{"name":"Bridge","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Bridge </em>creates a straight horizontal bridge 2&Prime; (4 yards) long and .5&Prime; (1 yard) wide, of immobile material that conforms to the surface it&rsquo;s cast upon. Thickness varies depending on what the bridge is made of, but is usually a few inches. When used to bridge a gap, both ends must touch a solid surface. The center does not need to be supported in any way.</p>\n<p>For all intents and purposes the <em>bridge </em>is a real, if temporary, structure. The <em>bridge </em>has a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Breaking Things]{Hardness} of 10, and may be destroyed as any other object (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Breaking Things]{Breaking Things}). The loss of a single segment causes catastrophic failure of the entire <em>bridge</em>, ending the spell. When the duration ends, the <em>bridge </em>vanishes without warning.</p>\n<p><em>Bridge </em>can be cast on an already solid floor, with effects varying by trapping. A flaming <em>bridge </em>gives all those crossing it a risk of catching @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fire]{fire} (check for each inch), an ice <em>bridge </em>is slippery (as rough ice), thorns count as difficult terrain, and so on. Check with the DM for what effect your trappings might have.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Damage (&ndash;1): </strong>The <em>bridge </em>causes 2d4 damage to anyone who contacts it.</li>\n<li><strong>Hardened (&ndash;1): </strong>The <em>bridge</em> is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Breaking Things]{Hardness} 12.</li>\n<li><strong>Size (&ndash;1): </strong>The length and width of the <em>bridge </em>doubles.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"–1","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"1 min/Rank","trapping":"Presenting holy symbol, calling in divine guidance","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_9ssl07b3tk","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"krHzOWh7MfjNdOXv"}
{"name":"Smite","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This power is cast on a weapon of some sort. If it&rsquo;s a ranged weapon, it affects one entire magazine, 20 bolts, shells, or arrows, or one full &ldquo;load&rdquo; of ammunition (the GM determines the exact quantity for unusual weapons). While the power is in effect, the weapon&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{damage}</span> is increased by +2, or +4 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (&ndash;1/&ndash;3/&ndash;5):</strong>&nbsp;Each additional individual target incurs an additional &minus;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}, or &minus;3 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template}, or &minus;5 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"–1","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"1 min/Rank","trapping":"A colored glow, runes, sigils, crackling energy, barbs grow from the blade","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"leQhkIBq7vFAFTPw"}
{"name":"Secret Writing","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Secret writing</em> requires ten minutes to cast and disguises the contents of a page, scroll, book or other suitable writing material, making it appear however the caster wishes. The caster must specify a command word when the spell is cast. Speaking the command word can reveal the true contents of the page or hide it again. Speaking the command word twice in rapid succession removes the spell completely. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Dispel]{Dispel} removes the effects of the spell and reveals the original contents of the page.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Suggestion (&minus;2): </strong>The caster can designate specific individuals who can read it automatically. To everyone else it appears as described above, but with an added effect of a non-harmful suggestion such as \"This scroll never existed.\" The suggestion must be defined when the power is activated. When the suggestion is triggered, the unauthorized reader must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by the caster's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll originally made to activate the power.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"–1","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","trapping":"Chanting while writing, enchanted paper, magically transcribed spoken words.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"mFHZCxGrRVNZPUlu"}
{"name":"Mind Reading","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Mind reading </em>is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts}. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} allows the character to gain one truthful answer from the subject. The target is aware of the mental intrusion unless the mind reader gets a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. The GM may apply @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{modifiers} based on the subject&rsquo;s mental @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} </span>or current state of mind.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"–2","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Psionic invasion, soulsight","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"nRtuNdyHUc0uJ1cO"}
{"name":"Tempest","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Tempest </em>can be used to create or dispel storms. If the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll is successful, an existing storm dissipates or a new one appears overhead with supernatural speed.</p>\n<p>The size of the storm affected is miles in diameter. The power only works outdoors. In areas where storms do not typically exist, such as a desert, the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll is made at &ndash;4 and may be attempted only once every 24 hours.</p>\n<p>When <em>tempest </em>is cast, the accompanying rain reduces visibility (treat as @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dark Lighting} conditions), extinguishes most normal fires within 1d10 rounds, and only volatile materials have a random chance of igniting from flame. <em>Tempest </em>conditions inflict a &ndash;1 penalty to most actions due to slipping, difficulty hearing, and so on. The Game Master must decide if any actions are unaffected.</p>\n<p>If the mage manages to score a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} when casting <em>tempest</em>, he has created a monstrous storm. Visibility is reduced to just 12\" (and still subject to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dark Lighting} ) and the ground turns into a quagmire. Any character running must make an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} roll or fall @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Prone]{prone} and become @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken}. Non-game effects include flash floods and lightning strikes, possibly damaging nearby buildings, drowning livestock, and flattening crops.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"–20","damage":"","range":"Sm in miles","duration":"2d6 hours","trapping":"Gestures, words of power.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_fstj95zcw9j","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"o5LJW17wYdZSKzN8"}
{"name":"Boost/Lower Trait","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This power allows a character to increase or decrease a target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait} (attribute or skill).</p>\n<p><em>Boosting </span></em>an ally&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait} increases the selected Trait one die type, or two with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, for five rounds.</p>\n<p><em>Lowering </span></em>an enemy&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait} has a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Powers]{Duration} of Instant and lowers the selected attribute or skill a die type with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success}, or two with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} (to a minimum of d4). A victim automatically tries to shake off the effect with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of his following turns.&nbsp;Success improves the effect one die type, and a raise removes the effect entirely.</p>\n<p>Additional castings don&rsquo;t stack on a single @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait} (take the highest), but may affect different </span>Traits.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><strong>Modifiers</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (&ndash;1/&ndash;3/&ndash;5):</strong>&nbsp;Each additional individual target incurs an additional &minus;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}, or &minus;3 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template}, or &minus;5 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li><strong>Strong (&ndash;2):</strong> <em>Lower Trait</em> only. The @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll to shake off the effect is made at &ndash;2.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"−1","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"1 min/Rank","trapping":"Physical change, glowing aura, potions","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"pjgH9DD2rmshvBlh"}
{"name":"Curse","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Some practitioners of the arcane arts heal their allies; others inflict sickness upon their enemies. To use this particularly nasty spell, the caster makes an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by the victim's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll. Failure means the victim suffers a level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} immediately. Each day at sunset the victim must make another @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} or suffer another level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} (further castings of curse have no additional effect).</p>\n<p>Once the accursed becomes @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Incapacitated}, he makes a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} roll each day to avoid death.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><strong>Breaking the Curse: </strong>The <em>curse</em> can be lifted by the original caster at will, and ends automatically if she's slain. <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Dispel]{Dispel}</em> also removes a curse, though each individual may only try once&mdash;if failed it's beyond her abilities.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"−3","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","trapping":"Voodoo doll, burning incense, vile curse spoken","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_9ssl07b3tk","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"q4gk6Idhq6R3fY61"}
{"name":"Lock/Unlock","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Whether guarding valuables or thwarting pursuers, <em>lock </em>allows the caster to seal a door, treasure chest, or other object with a lock. Attempts to pick or smash the lock suffer a &minus;2 penalty, &minus;4 if the caster got a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on the casting roll. Also, the locked object gains +2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Breaking Things]{Toughness}, +4 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. The wizard may open his own locks normally. Opening the <em>lock</em> by any means automatically ends the spell.</p>\n<p><em>Unlock </em>opens any mundane lock, though if the lock is particularly complex, the GM may assign penalties to the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll. A door sealed with <em>lock </em>gives a &ndash;2 or &ndash;4 penalty to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} rolls to cast this spell.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Strong (&ndash;2): </strong>For an additional &minus;2 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}&nbsp;the strength of the spell is increased. The <em>lock </em>is subject to a &minus;4 modifier to break or open the object, and an <em>unlock </em>recieves +2 to the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"–2","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Special (lock); Instant (Unlock)","trapping":"Whispered words, scattering dust on a door, aura around lock, tapping a lock three times.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"qkvTWWoJBxzpBG63"}
{"name":"Telekinesis","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Telekinesis </em>is the ability to move objects or creatures (including oneself) with arcane will. It has a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} of d10, or d12 with a raise.</span></p>\n<p>Unwilling opponents resist the caster&rsquo;s </span>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill}</span> with an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll when targeted and at the start of each of their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{turns} afterward until they&rsquo;re released. They can be moved up to the caster&rsquo; @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} per turn in any direction, and can be bashed into walls, ceilings, or other obstacles for Str+d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{damage}</span>. Dropped creatures suffer @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Falling]{falling damage} as usual.</p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>Telekinetic Tools</strong>: </span>A caster can wield tools (including weapons) with </span><em>telekinesis </em>as an action. Use the caster&rsquo;s relevant</span> @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{skill} when attacking in this way (not his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill}).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"–3","damage":"","range":"Sm x2","duration":"1 min/Rank","trapping":"A wave of the hand, magic wand, steely gaze","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_9ssl07b3tk","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"romigFY9bR4WXRIu"}
{"name":"Mind Link","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><em>Mind link&nbsp;</em>creates a telepathic connection between two individuals (which does not necessarily have to include the caster). The link accommodates only willing subjects and communication&mdash;thoughts that aren&rsquo;t consciously transmitted aren&rsquo;t relayed.</span></p>\n<p>Once @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{activated}, the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Range}</span>&nbsp;between all linked minds is one mile, or five with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</span></p>\n<p>If any of the linked characters suffers a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}</span>, all others must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} roll or be @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken}&nbsp;</span>(this cannot cause a&nbsp;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}</span>).</p>\n<p>The speed of communication is that of normal speech, but with a&nbsp;</span>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}&nbsp;members may communicate up to 30 seconds or so of speech on a single combat turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (&ndash;1/&ndash;3/&ndash;5):</strong>&nbsp;Each additional individual target incurs an additional &minus;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}, or &minus;3 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template}, or &minus;5 for everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"–1","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"1 hour/Rank","trapping":"Headpieces, talismans, of Tao or other gods, crystals","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_raamp2usckl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"_id":"sg6mUYs86RNysmRv"}
